<TITLE> Market opens downbeat </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 05 (bdnews24.com)The market opened downbeat Wednesday after gaining the previous day. It recovered losses after the first hour of trade, but fell again during midday trade. At 12.51 pm, the DGEN or general index was down 19.76 points or 0.68 percent at 2885.42. The DSI or all-share price index was at 2438.58, down 17.49 points or 0.71 percent. Of the issues traded, 73 advanced, 131 declined and 13 remained unchanged. At 12.58 pm BRAC Bank was selling down at Tk 1519.75 from Tuesday's Tk 1541.5. UCBL had also declined, selling at Tk 4630 from its previous day's closing of Tk 4797.5 Islami Bank Perpetual Bond declined to Tk 1515 from Tk 1518.5. Summit Power continued to rally. It was selling up at Tk 1436.25 from Tuesday's Tk 1427.75. Uttara Bank fell after gaining the previous day. It was selling at Tk 4585 from its previous day's closing price of Tk 4608.5. Other scrips on the top ten by share value board BOC Bangladesh, Square Pharma, Power Grid Company of Bangladesh and Trust Bankalso declined, while Islami Bank rose. bdn
